5|$|The Rally to Restore Sanity and/or Fear was a {{gathering}} {{that took place}} on October 30, 2010, at the National Mall in Washington, D.C. The rally was led by <b>Jon</b> <b>Stewart,</b> host of the satirical news program The Daily Show, and Stephen Colbert, in-character as a conservative political pundit. About 215,000 people attended the rally, according to aerial photography analysis by AirPhotosLive.com for CBS News.|$|E
